<quantity box="[451,601,484,510]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="3.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="mm" value="4.6" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="3.9">3.9– 5.3 mm</quantity>
. Distinguished by the small eyes (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1118,484,510]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="2.[264,382,1704,1728]" captionTargetBox="[264,1323,481,1673]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,481,1678]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Head (1, 3, and 5) and parameres (2, 4, and 6) in dorsal view. 1 – 2. Trichillum heydeni. 3 – 4. T. hirsutum. 5 – 6. Pedaridium bidens." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273246/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Fig. 
<number box="[1103,1118,484,510]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) combined with equilateral clypeal teeth and impunctate elytral striae. This species is adequately described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira" box="[300,606,564,590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" refString="Ferreira, A. M. R. M. &amp; M. H. M. Galileo. (1993) Revisao taxonomica do genero Pedaridium Harold, 1868 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Scarabaeinae, Coprini). Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 74, 3 - 70." type="journal article" year="1993">
Ferreira &amp; Galileo (
<number box="[533,597,564,590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
